Quote: (The Ohinemuri Deputation) Eicke's constitution, we hear,/ Was so delicate .../ That on the journey he'd be queer,/ Unless sustained by bottled beer;/ Simpson said pulling [sc. rowing] made him dry,/ .../ .../ So of grog they took a good supply/ When they went to Ohinemuri./ [33] Their life was one continual shout,/ They stayed up there and idled about/ .../ But the beer and the grog was running out./ Of course they'd had many a <i>korero</i> [kore|ro],/ Which led to nothing at all ...
